To establish a connection with USB device between two computers we usually use USB cables. They are fairly reliable and provide fast and secure access to the deviceâ€™s content or functionality. However we are all aware of the limitation they have, i.e. distance limitation, you can only run them as far as the length of the cable permits. Luckily there are numerous ways to overcome it - extension cables, wireless USB extenders, network converters, wireless USB cable, wireless USB hub and [USB sharing software](https://www.flexihub.com/usb-over-wifi.html).
